## Dark mode color systems for elite positioning

For tech/health consultants targeting high-performers, **dark mode is now the premium default**. However, pure black (#000000) is fading—premium 2026 sites use rich charcoals and warm off-blacks that feel sophisticated without causing eye strain.

**The "Elite Operator" dark palette:**
```
Background:         #0D0D0D
Surface:            #1A1A1A  
Surface Elevated:   #242424
Border:             #333333
Text Primary:       #FFFFFF
Text Secondary:     #A0A0A0
Text Muted:         #666666
Accent Primary:     #3B82F6 (trust/tech blue)
Accent Alt:         #FF6B35 (energy/action orange)
Success:            #10B981
Warning:            #F59E0B
```

**Single accent color is mandatory.** Elite sites use one accent maximum—multiple accent colors signal amateur design. The choice between electric blue (#3B82F6) and bold orange (#FF6B35) depends on positioning: blue for trust/authority, orange for energy/disruption.

**For light mode alternatives** (clinical/medical positioning):
```
Background:         #FAFAFA
Surface:            #FFFFFF
Border:             #E5E7EB
Text Primary:       #111827 (not pure black)
Text Secondary:     #6B7280
```

**Gradient trends remain active** but evolved—mesh gradients with organic flow and soft-glow ambient effects replace harsh rainbow blends. Use sparingly for hero sections and feature highlights.

