## Typography that commands authority

The typography stack determines whether a site reads as "executive advisor" or "freelance consultant." **2026 favors variable fonts** for performance and precision control.

**The recommended "authority" stack:**

| Use Case | Font | Weight | Signal |
|----------|------|--------|--------|
| Headlines | **Satoshi** | 700 | Modern premium, geometric |
| Body | **Inter** | 400-500 | Industry standard, GitHub/Figma use |
| Data/Code | **Geist Mono** | 400 | Technical precision |

**Alternative pairings for specific positioning:**
- **Enterprise professional:** IBM Plex Sans (600 heading, 400 body)
- **Technical innovator:** Space Grotesk heading + Inter body
- **Warm authority:** Playfair Display (serif heading) + Source Sans Pro body

**Size specifications for premium hierarchy:**
```
H1: 48-60px, Bold (700), line-height 1.1
H2: 36-42px, SemiBold (600), line-height 1.2
H3: 24-30px, SemiBold (600), line-height 1.3
Body: 17-18px, Regular (400), line-height 1.65
```

**Critical rule:** Maximum content width of **650-720px for prose**. Wider feels amateur. Patrick Collison-style sites constrain content aggressively with 20%+ margins on desktop.

