## Standout consultant sites that nail elite positioning

Analysis of high-converting personal brand sites reveals clear patterns separating "elite operator" from "generic consultant."

**Rich Litvin (richlitvin.com)** sets the standard for premium coaching. His positioning—"I Make Even Millionaires Uncomfortable"—pairs with transparent ultra-premium pricing ($40K-$250K/year displayed openly). Black backgrounds with gold accents signal luxury. His "Why You Shouldn't Work With Me" page creates deliberate exclusivity. Named clients with specific titles and dollar results ($300K in half a year) beat generic testimonials.

**Ben Greenfield Life (bengreenfieldlife.com)** demonstrates bio-hacker positioning done right. Celebrity testimonials from Rick Rubin, Zac Efron, and Wim Hof establish immediate credibility. The application-based coaching model ("Apply" not "Sign Up") signals selectivity. Forest green accents on white create a scientific-yet-approachable feel.

**David C. Baker (davidcbaker.com)** shows radical transparency working—full pricing visible, "paid upfront, no refunds, no references" terms signal confidence. Content depth lets prospects "get inside his head" before engaging.

**Dr. Alka Patel (dralkapatel.com)** bridges medical credentials with longevity consulting through "Exceptional lives demand exceptional care" positioning. MD credentials combine with personal transformation narrative for both authority and relatability.

**The elite positioning formula:**
- **Selective language:** "Apply" vs "Sign Up"; "By Invitation" vs "Book Now"
- **Transparent premium pricing:** High fees displayed openly create anchor effect
- **Named social proof:** Specific individuals with titles > generic testimonials > logo bars
- **Counter-positioning:** "Why NOT to work with me" creates intrigue and self-selection
- **Tiered offerings:** Begin → Mastery → Elite pathways accommodate different readiness levels

