## Implementation blueprint for elite operator positioning

**Complete design system specification:**

```css
/* Colors - Dark Mode Primary */
--bg-primary: #0D0D0D;
--bg-surface: #1A1A1A;
--bg-elevated: #242424;
--border: #333333;
--text-primary: #FFFFFF;
--text-secondary: #A0A0A0;
--accent: #3B82F6;

/* Typography */
--font-heading: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
--font-body: 'Inter', sans-serif;
--font-mono: 'Geist Mono', monospace;

/* Spacing */
--section-padding: 120px;
--content-max-width: 680px;
--card-radius: 8px;
```

**Page structure hierarchy:**
1. **Navigation:** Text-only horizontal, no dropdowns
2. **Hero:** Bold positioning statement, no hero image (anti-hero pattern)
3. **Problem statement:** "The expensive problem you solve"
4. **Credibility:** Named testimonials with specific results + media logos
5. **Offerings:** Tiered pathways with application-based CTAs
6. **Content:** Essays/ideas demonstrating depth of thinking
7. **Contact:** Plain text email, no elaborate forms

**Technical requirements:**
- Load time under 2 seconds
- Static site or minimal CMS (Hugo, Ghost, Astro)
- GSAP + ScrollTrigger for animation
- Custom cursor with contextual states
- `prefers-reduced-motion` respect for accessibility
- RSS feed available (signals substance over flash)

The fundamental principle across all elite sites: **design that appears effortless signals you're too valuable to fuss with appearances**. The restraint itself becomes the brand statement—sophisticated minimalism that says "I build things that matter" louder than any hero image could.